          <h3>üå± Early Roots</h3>
          <p>I was raised in the early 80s, learning independence the hard way while trying to figure out who I was. My childhood was a mixed bag: a half-brother 10 years older first sparked my love of music by blasting the good stuff from the late 80s and early 90s.</p>
          <p>After my parents divorced and I lost contact with my dad and brother, I moved to a beef farm with my mom and stepdad. Life there was full of animals ‚Äî steers, calves, pigs, goats, even llamas ‚Äî and I loved every second of it. I showed steers at the county fair, and those memories still make me smile.</p>
