          <p>I met Blake in college through a friend who grew up with him. After our first date, I told my resident (RA): ‚ÄúI‚Äôm gonna marry this guy.‚Äù And I did ‚Äî in 2006. Almost 20 years later, he‚Äôs still my biggest cheerleader: the one who gets me, accepts the chaos, helps me navigate family drama, and teaches me new ways to communicate and live with more grace.</p>
          <p>In 2010, Porter arrived and I went full mom-mode. None of my friends were in the same stage, so I turned to a brand-new platform: YouTube. Back then it was all community, no algorithms, and I found my people in the TTC and mommy groups.</p>
        </article>

